OL,3,CFirst cases of bluetongue found in
OL,4,Csheep in Wales
OL,6,FBluetongue-3 has been detected in
OL,7,FWales and follows BTV-3 cases in the
OL,8,Feast of England over the last month.
OL,10,FFarmers are being urged to be vigilant
OL,11,Ffor the disease and practice safe
OL,12,Fsourcing of livestock.
OL,14,FBluetongue is caused by a virus that
OL,15,Fis primarily transmitted by certain
OL,16,Fspecies of biting midges. It affects
OL,17,Fruminants (like cattle, goats, sheep
OL,18,Fand deer) and camelids (like alpacas
OL,19,Fand llamas).
