OL,3,CFirst cases of bluetongue found in
OL,4,Csheep in Wales
OL,6,FBluetongue does not affect people or
OL,7,Ffood safety. Further investigations
OL,8,Fare taking place on the farm affected
OL,9,Fto determine whether additional
OL,10,Fcontrols are needed.
OL,12,FGavin Watkins, the deputy chief
OL,13,Fveterinary officer, said: "The cases
OL,14,Fidentified in Gwynedd are from animals
OL,15,Fbrought into Wales.
OL,17,F"We will apply measures to stop the
OL,18,Fdisease spreading from these three
OL,19,Fsheep and our aim remains to keep
OL,20,FWales free of bluetongue.
