OL,3,CFirst cases of bluetongue found in
OL,4,Csheep in Wales
OL,6,F"It is important to talk to your vet
OL,7,Fand practice safe-sourcing of
OL,8,Flivestock, to protect our herds and
OL,9,Fflocks and keep any further disease
OL,10,Fout of Wales.
OL,12,F"I would urge all farmers and others
OL,13,Fwho keep ruminants and camelids to be
OL,14,Fvigilant for the signs of bluetongue
OL,15,Fand to report any suspect cases to
OL,16,FAPHA immediately.
OL,18,F"We have been raising awareness of the
OL,19,Fdisease with vets and industry and
OL,20,Fappreciate their help in communicating
OL,21,Fthe risks to animal keepers in Wales."
